SPECS – Toyota GR Supra (3.0L turbo, 2025‑era)
Price (typical / base for GR Supra 3.0L): ~ ₱ 5,550,000 (Philippine‑market 3.0L A/T)
Overall Dimensions (mm): 4,379 × 1,854 × 1,299 Wheelbase (mm): 2,470 Seating Capacity: 2
ENGINE & PERFORMANCE
Engine Type: 6‑Cylinder, In‑Line, 24‑Valve DOHC, chain drive, with VVT (IN/EX)
Engine Displacement (cc): 2,998
Maximum Output (metric): 387 ps @ 5,800–6,500 rpm
Maximum Torque (Nm): 500 Nm @ 1,800–5,000 rpm
Fuel Type: Gasoline
Drivetrain: Rear‑Wheel Drive
Transmission Options:
6‑Speed Manual (with IMT)
8‑Speed Automatic
PERFORMANCE (approximate, AT version)
0–60 mph (0–≈ 97 km/h): ~ 3.9 seconds
Top Speed (electronically limited): ~ 250 km/h (≈ 155 mph)
CHASSIS / WHEELS / BRAKES
Suspension (front): MacPherson strut
Suspension (rear): Multi‑link
Wheels / Tires (stock): Front 255/35 R19, Rear 275/35 R19 (for 19" forged‑aluminum wheels)
Front Brakes: Ventilated discs with fixed 4‑piston calipers
Rear Brakes: Ventilated discs with floating calipers
INTERIOR & FEATURES (common for 3.0L trim / premium spec)
Seats: 2 — Sports seats (driver: 8‑way power w/ memory; passenger: 8‑way power)
Upholstery: Alcantara (or equivalent premium‑sport material)
Headlamps: LED with DRL (Daytime Running Lights)
Drive Modes: Normal / Sport (varies by market and trim)
Fuel Tank Capacity: ~52 L
